<h1>AI Origins Protocol Specification</h1>
<p class="muted">Reference specification for node identity, transport model, and admission logic used by the AI Origins network.</p>

<div class="card">
<h2>Specification Index</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>/spec/node/v1</strong> — node identity specification</li>
<li><strong>/spec/network/v1</strong> — network topology and transport model</li>
<li><strong>/spec/admission/v1</strong> — node admission states and verification model</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2 id="node-v1">Node Specification v1</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>This specification defines the machine-readable identity required for a node to participate in the AI Origins network.</p>

<h3>Required fields</h3>
<ul>
<li>node_id</li>
<li>node_role</li>
<li>region</li>
<li>transport type</li>
<li>public_key</li>
<li>endpoint</li>
</ul>

<h3>Example</h3>
<pre>{
"schema":"https://aiorigins.org/spec/node/v1",
"node_id":"fixed-qingdao-01",
"node_role":"fixed",
"region":"CN-QD",
"transport":{
  "type":"wireguard",
  "wg_address":"10.66.66.10/32",
  "endpoint":"qingdao.example.net:51820",
  "public_key":"BASE64_PUBLIC_KEY"
}
}</pre>

<p class="muted">Nodes may include additional metadata fields, but the required identity attributes must be present for verification.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="network-v1">Network Specification v1</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>The AI Origins network uses a private mesh transport model with role-based address allocation.</p>

<h3>Transport</h3>
<ul>
<li>Transport type: WireGuard</li>
<li>Private mesh range: 10.66.66.0/24</li>
</ul>

<h3>Address allocation</h3>
<pre>
10.66.66.1      core
10.66.66.10-19  fixed nodes
10.66.66.20-29  mobile nodes
10.66.66.30-39  reserve nodes
10.66.66.40-49  edge/service nodes
</pre>

<h3>Minimal network shape</h3>
<pre>
            core-london
               │
      ┌────────┼────────┐
      │                 │
fixed-helsinki     fixed-qingdao
</pre>

<p class="muted">Additional nodes may expand along Eurasian corridors without changing the protocol model.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="admission-v1">Admission Specification v1</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>Nodes joining the network must pass verification before admission.</p>

<h3>Status model</h3>
<ul>
<li>PASS — compatible with protocol rules</li>
<li>WARN — minor issues but acceptable</li>
<li>FAIL — incompatible with policy</li>
</ul>

<h3>Join flow</h3>
<pre>
prepare node.json
→ deploy node
→ run join-check
→ PASS / WARN / FAIL
→ admission review
→ node activated
</pre>
</div>

